name: phosphoribosylformylglycinamidine synthase
classes: Carbon-nitrogen ligases with glutamine as amido-N-donor
reaction: ATP + N2-formyl-N1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide + L-glutamine + H2O = ADP + phosphate + 2-(formamido)-N1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)acetamidine + L-glutamate [RN:R04463]

references.title: Biosynthesis of the purines. XIV. Conversion of (alpha-N-formyl) glycinamide ribotide to (alpha-N-formyl) glycinamidine ribotide; purification and requirements of the enzyme system.
